{"id":"godeploy-api-62e","title":"Document nginx proxy server in architecture docs","description":"The godeploy-nginx-server repo is missing from architecture documentation. It's the edge proxy that:\n- Routes subdomain requests (project--tenant.spa.godeploy.app) to DO Spaces CDN\n- Handles custom domain routing\n- Serves marketing site (godeploy.app)\n- Implements SPA fallback (serves index.html for client-side routing)\n- Caches responses from CDN\n\nNeed to:\n1. Update docs/architecture/overview.md to include nginx in system diagram\n2. Add nginx server block to monorepo structure (or note it's separate repo)\n3. Document the request flow: User → Nginx → DO Spaces CDN\n4. Explain the 3 server blocks: subdomains, marketing, custom domains","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-19T11:07:46.639576575-05:00","updated_at":"2025-12-19T11:15:49.171619174-05:00","closed_at":"2025-12-19T11:15:49.17162207-05:00"}
